To set up MySQL replication:
1. Configure MySQL master:
   ```bash
   mysql -u root -p
   CHANGE MASTER TO MASTER_HOST='master_host', MASTER_USER='replication_user', MASTER_PASSWORD='password';
   START SLAVE;
   ```
2. Check slave status:
   ```bash
   SHOW SLAVE STATUS\G;
   ```
3. If replication fails, restart it:
   ```bash
   STOP SLAVE;
   RESET SLAVE;
   START SLAVE;
   ```

Run the following Impala queries:
```bash
SELECT COUNT(*), par_dt FROM energy_efficiency.cell WHERE par_dt > '202111201' GROUP BY par_dt ORDER BY par_dt DESC;
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM (SELECT DISTINCT * FROM energy_efficiency.cell WHERE par_dt='20211210') a;
```
